      <hedline>
        <hl1>RECORD PROFIT AT PETROBRAS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Jennifer L. Rich</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Rich, Jennifer L</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Brazilian state oil company Petroleo Brasileiro, or Petrobras, posted record profit of $2.5 billion for first half of year, in contrast to loss of $555 million a year earlier; first-half revenue rose 82 percent, to $11 billion, from $6.1 billion last year (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Capitalizing on soaring prices, the Brazilian state oil company Petroleo Brasileiro, or Petrobras, posted a record profit of $2.5 billion in the first half of the year, in contrast to a loss of $555 million a year earlier. The company's first-half revenue rose 82 percent, to $11 billion, from $6.1 billion last year. The Brazilian government sold $4.4 billion in Petrobras stock last week.</p>
        <p>Jennifer L. Rich</p>
      </block>
